challengeName: Genpact Email Classification Ideation Contest Statement
detailedRequirements:
Welcome to this ideation challenge, please read on for details! Please note that this is an ideation challenge - there will be a checkpoint you can submit for in order to receive feedback and potentially one of five $100 prizes - we've detailed exactly what we're expecting as outputs below.

Genpact support representatives receive a lot of emails about various different matters. The current method by which the firm processes them and determines  their content appears below.

A workflow system receives emails at a generic support address (e.g., support@genpact.com).

The email is captured as a support ticket.

Support Reps read and classify the email into categories like “Invoice”,”Payment”, “FYI”,”Technical Issue”, etc.

Some of the data from the email is retyped or manually copied and pasted into fields on the case. For example, an email classified as “Invoice” might include data such as invoice number and amount of payment.

This highly manual process isn’t scalable, and Genpact wants your ideas on how to automate it.

Objective

Propose proprietary and/or open-source software and algorithms that could be used to extract important data from emails sent to Genpact and to classify them based on their contents.
finalSubmissionGuidelines:
Data Description

Genpact has provided 331 email threads (available from a link in the forums) like those they receive routinely. Some threads contain only 1 message, while others contain multiple messages. Each has been classified as 1 of 37 types.

Classifications: AP processing errors, Audit request, Bank queries, Bank rejections, BMG, CBCP escalation, CBCP request, Claim status, Concur issues, Contract Related, Credit Card Maintenance, FYI, GL requests/ PC uplifts, Invoice Status, Invoices for scan, JBA/SMF Maintenance, Manual payment request, Matching Report, Missing documents/ supporting documentation, Non AP documents Non PO Invoices (coding information, VAT), OIR, Open Item reports, Other, out of office messages, Payment confirmation, Payment reminder, Payments (MPR, urgent payment requests, BMG), PO related, Process updates, Proof of payment, Recall, Two Way match report, Urgent payment request, Vendor master data, Vendor statement, Web Ex Trainings

Contemplated Architecture

Genpact wants to deploy the algorithm on Salesforce.com. Furthermore, the firm needs the solution to run on multiple different instances of Salesforce.com, each belonging to a different client and having its own data. As a result, both the number of categories in the Classification variable and the categories themselves may vary by client.

Scoring

You will be judged on the quality of your ideas, the quality of your description of the principle(s) of the ideas, and how much benefit it can provide for the client.  

You will also be judged on how clearly you describe your idea. The winner will be selected by the client, not the Topcoder review board.

The winner will be chosen by the most logical and convincing reasoning as to how and why the idea presented will meet the objective.

Requirements to Win a Prize 

Checkpoint - Five Prizes of $100 - Important Notes

In order to be eligible for a checkpoint prize you must submit to this challenge by Thursday 17th March at 7pm EST. Any submission timestamped before then will be eligible and considered in the running for a prize for both the checkpoint and final submission. After this time you will only be eligible for final submission prizes.

The advantages of submitting to the checkpoint phase will be client feedback around your ideas and the opportunity to receive one of the five $100 checkpoint prizes.

You are not required to submit for the checkpoint in order to submit for the final phase.

Final Submission

Achieve a passing score in the top 5. See the “Scoring” section above. 

Submit a complete report at least 2 pages long outlining your proposal. The required content appears in the “Report” section below. 

Report 

Your report must be at least 2 pages long, be in Word or PDF format, and contain at least the following sections. 

Software

If your proposal involves multiple programs working together from different vendors or a combination of proprietary and open-source solutions, then please complete the following for each part;

  • Name
  • Version
  • Vendor (if proprietary)
  • Estimated annual cost (if proprietary)
  • Links to licensing information

Algorithms

If your proposal involves proprietary software, then some of the following may not be easy to find. Do your best. However, if you propose an open source solution, then we expect you to complete all of the following.

  • Algorithm name
  • Brief written description
  • Evidence of successful past implementations
  • Steps in pseudo-code
  • Extraction and use of the ID, System, Other ID, Sender Email, Count, To Email, and Subject
  • Creation of new variables, if applicable
  • Method of estimation of Classification probability
  • How it will run on multiple different instances of Salesforce.com, each belonging to a different client and having its own data
  • How it will handle new categories that might be added to the Classification variable
  • How it might incorporate feedback on Classification errors 
  • References to papers, if applicable
  • Advantages and disadvantages of the approach chosen 
  • Degree of scalability and justification for your assessment thereof
